From 8282f0f8ecf8b847e5964a308e041ba3b049811c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jonathan Albrecht <jonathan.albrecht@ibm.com>
Date: Wed, 4 Feb 2026 07:28:29 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] Fix an endian problem in upb that caused protoc plugins to
 crash on big endian platforms (#25363)

The protobuf build started failing on big endian platforms (I'm using s390x) starting with v33.0. The cmake build would fail when running `protoc` to compile test files. The errors looked like:

```bash
gmake[2]: *** [CMakeFiles/upb-test.dir/build.make:85: google/protobuf/any.upb.h] Error 1
--upb_out: protoc-gen-upb: Plugin killed by signal 11.
```

I did a git bisect and the crash started with commit c36f728a3e4352d887f82d53dda330972b27dbf7. The fix is to add a `_upb_Decoder_MungeInt32(val)` call on the closed enum value so it can be decoded properly later.

I think this might fix https://github.com/protocolbuffers/protobuf/issues/24103 but I'm not able to test it.

Closes #25363

COPYBARA_INTEGRATE_REVIEW=https://github.com/protocolbuffers/protobuf/pull/25363 from linux-on-ibm-z:upb-decode-endian 714383464de5bafdafafa7e5b0ad3a9c92287b45
PiperOrigin-RevId: 865398323
---
 upb/wire/decode.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/upb/wire/decode.c b/upb/wire/decode.c
index 55420a3a128e7..9b050866b45ea 100644
--- upb/wire/decode.c
+++ upb/wire/decode.c
@@ -938,6 +938,7 @@ const char* _upb_Decoder_DecodeWireValue(upb_Decoder* d, const char* ptr,
           *op = kUpb_DecodeOp_UnknownField;
           return ptr;
         }
+        _upb_Decoder_MungeInt32(val);
       } else {
         _upb_Decoder_Munge(field, val);
       }
